-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Banco do Brasil, Dasa, Embraer
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-02-14T15:39:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/brazilian-stock-movers-banco-do-brasil-dasa-embraer.html
The following companies are having
 unusual  price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:57 p.m. local time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index fell 0.4 percent to 65,438.99.  Banco do Brasil SA  (BBAS3 BS) advanced 2.5 percent to 27.04
reais.  Latin America ’s biggest bank by assets reported fourth-
quarter earnings that beat analysts’ estimates as loans grew 20
percent, faster than the industry average. Adjusted earnings per
share reached 4.11 reais ($2.39), above the 3.92 reais average
of 15 estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  Diagnosticos da America SA  (DASA3 BS) fell 4 percent to
15.50 reais. The medical-diagnostics firm known as Dasa said
Chief Financial Officer Jose Mauricio Mora Puliti is leaving to
“pursue new challenges.” Chief Executive Officer Marcelo Noll Barboza will fill the position.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) gained 0.9 percent to 12.58 reais.
The world’s fourth-biggest planemaker said it sold 12 commercial
jets and three business aircraft at the Singapore Air Show. At
list prices, the deals are worth $680.6 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
